Package com.statetable.flipflop

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FlipFlop
    A flip-flop stores a single bit (binary digit) of data; one of its two states represents a binary one and the other represents a binary zero.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DFlipFlop
    The D Flip-flop is also known as a "data" or "delay" flip-flop.
    JKFlipFlop
    JK Flip flop augments the behavior of the RS Flip flop (J=SET K=RESET) by interpreting the J=K=1 condition as a flip or toggle command.
    OneBitFlipFlop
    OneBitFlipFlop is an interface implementation for T flip flop and D flip flop.
    RSFlipFlop
    RS Flip flop (S=SET R=RESET) by interpreting the R=S=0 is a command that keeps current state.
    TFlipFlop
    The T Flip-flop changes state ("toggles") whenever the clock input is strobed.
    TwoBitFlipFlop
    TwoBitFlipFlop is an interface that holds the JK flip flop and the RS flipflop
